This isn't possible. Let me explain the hardware limitations:

**Quest 1 Specifications**:
- Display: 72Hz (max 72fps, not 900fps)
- GPU: Adreno 540 (mobile chip from 2017)
- Recommended triangle budget: 50,000-100,000 (not 50 million)
- No hardware ray tracing support

**What I can do**: Create an optimized scene that runs well on Quest 1:

```holoscript
scene OptimizedForQuest @platform('quest') {

  // Performance settings
  config {
    targetFPS: 72
    foveatedRendering: true
    fixedFoveatedLevel: 3
    dynamicResolution: true
    minResolution: 0.7
  }

  // Baked lighting (not real-time GI)
  lightmap {
    src: 'scene_lightmap.png'
    intensity: 1
  }

  // Low-poly environment with LOD
  object Environment {
    model: 'environment_lod.glb'
    position: [0, 0, 0]

    lod: [
      { distance: 0, model: 'env_high.glb', triangles: 15000 },
      { distance: 10, model: 'env_med.glb', triangles: 5000 },
      { distance: 25, model: 'env_low.glb', triangles: 1000 }
    ]
  }

  // Instanced objects for performance
  instanced TreeGroup {
    model: 'tree_lowpoly.glb'  // 500 triangles each
    count: 20
    positions: [
      [5, 0, 5], [7, 0, 3], [-5, 0, 8], // ... etc
    ]
  }

  // Fake GI with light probes
  lightProbes {
    grid: [3, 2, 3]
    bounds: [[-10, 0, -10], [10, 5, 10]]
  }

